                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 4.  <span>X-ray structure of the proline-rich pentapeptide (4<em>S</em>)-FPro54-Val55-(4<em>S</em>)-FPro56-Trp57-(4<em>S</em>)-FPro58 (PVPWP).</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.fig3.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.fig3.caption1.p1"></a><p>The continuous electron density (grey, 2Fo-Fc; contouring levels 1 σ) indicates fluorine atoms at the 4<em>S</em>-position in three buried Pro residues (54, 56, 58). Their experimental electron densities are localized unambiguously (image preparation with PYMOL (<a href="http://pymol.sourceforge.net/">http://pymol.sourceforge.net/</a>)). Out of the three Pro residues forming <em>trans</em> peptide bonds, only Pro56 exhibits predominant C<sup>γ</sup>-<em>exo</em> pucker whereas the other two have pyrrolidine rings with C<sup>γ</sup>-<em>endo</em> conformation. The rigid local secondary structure of this motif forces the (4<em>S</em>)-fluorinated pyrrolidine ring of (4<em>S</em>)-FPro56 into a stereochemically unfavorable C<sup>γ</sup>-<em>exo</em> pucker.</p>
